{"word":"ἀυτμή","slug":"ἀυτμή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀυτμή</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄημι'><el>ἄημι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>breath</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>ἀϋτμὴ Ἡφαίστοιο</el> <i>the fiery breath of</i> Hephaestus, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>πυρὸς ἀϋτμή</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; of bellows, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; of wind, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>odour, scent, fragrance</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}